# Train with noise 

`train_with_noise.py` trains the Simplified Transformer on the LTL dataset while injecting **noise into the training sequences only** (validation/test remain clean), then compares metrics across noise levels/types and saves results.

## Noise types
- `replacement`: replace selected symbols with random symbols
- `deletion`: length-preserving (implemented as replacement)
- `insertion`: length-preserving (implemented as replacement)
- `swap`: swap adjacent symbols
- `shuffle`: shuffle symbols within a chosen subset of positions
- `mixed`: 50% replacement + 50% swap

`noise_level` is the fraction of positions affected (e.g., `0.1` = ~10% of symbols corrupted).

## Run
Example (single noise type, multiple levels):

python3 train_with_noise.py \
  --csv_path semester2_transformer/dataset/dataset_33.csv \
  --json_path semester2_transformer/dataset/formula_33.json \
  --noise_types replacement \
  --noise_levels 0.0 0.1 0.2 0.3 \
  --epochs 15 \
  --batch_size 64 \
  --lr 0.001 \
  --output results_noise.json \
  --plot_dir plots_noise
